Just for my understanding on 2744c5c , you're saying this would be true on PyPy?
```python
>>> a = 1.2
>>> b = 1.2
>>> a is b
False
```

@chris-b1 about is-ness, yes that is True
```
>>>> a = float('nan')
>>>> b = float('nan')
>>>> a is b
True
>>>> a=1.2
>>>> b=1.2
>>>> a is b
True
```
on cpython both are False
